KAIZER Chiefs are in the top-eight! Agutsy 2-1 win over fierce rivals Mamelodi Sundowns at Loftus yesterday, not only pushed them into the top-eight, but also ended Sundowns' unbeaten run. Goals from substitutes Samir Nurkovic and Dumsani Zuma secured the win. Gaston Sirino rounded Khune to open the scoring in the 35th minute, but two goals in quick succession midway through the second half, turned the game on its head and as Amakhosi stunned the hosts.         